- The board uses `routingDisabled` and also sets `autorouter="disabled"` on the root board in `index.tsx:12`.
- The circuit includes a USB-C receptacle, RP2040, a GPIO25-driven LED with 1k resistor, and basic decoupling plus bulk caps in `index.tsx:17`.
- I assumed a minimal power scheme with `VBUS -> VREG_IN`, `VREG_VOUT -> V3V3`, all I/O rails tied to `V3V3`, both DVDD rails tied to `V1V1`, `RUN` pulled high directly, and `TESTEN` tied low in `index.tsx:67`.
- USB data lines are connected from the USB-C connector to the RP2040 USB pins, shell and ground pins are tied to `GND`, and CC/SBU pins are exposed as named nets without extra circuitry in `index.tsx:49`.
